commitResults.messageBody:
Assume single task number to follow marking or delete commands

A marking or delete command works even when task numbers are separated by whitespaces

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge pull request #1 from rayray39/branch-A-Assertions
Parser.java: Abstract out complicated boolean expression
commitResults.messageBody:
Boolean expression to check for invalid user command is too complicated to write in one line

Abstracting out the boolean expression into a public method makes it more readable

Let's abstract those complicated boolean expressions into their own public methods to make the code more readable

commitResults.messageTitle: Parser.java: Abstract out complicated boolean expression
commitResults.messageBody:
Boolean expressions to check for invalid or absent task number are too complicated and unreadable

Abstract out the boolean expression into public methods make them more readable

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code by abstracting complicated boolean expressions
commitResults.messageBody:
Too many boolean expressions to check for validity of user command

Many boolean expressions are being used in different areas of Parser.java to check for validity of user commands and this makes it hard to track and read.

Let's abstract the boolean expressions into methods to make them more readable and package it into a single method that can be easily called

Add exception handling for view command
commitResults.messageBody:
Parser.java should handle all the exception handling and process invalid user commands. View command's exception handling is processed inside TaskList.java which is not the responsibility of TaskList.java.

Let's transfer the responsibility of processing the validity of view command from TaskList.java to Parser.java

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove scheduledDate attribute from Task
commitResults.messageBody:
ToDo class, which inherits Task, does not need access to the scheduledDate attribute. Only ScheduledTask inheritors, Deadline and Event, will require access to scheduledDate.

This removes the need to explicitly check for Deadline or Event objects in viewScheduledTasks method in TaskList. Makes the code more readable and maintanable.

Let's remove the scheduledDate attribute from Task and add it into ScheduledTask.
